"Ancient Vessels of the Future" BirdDogg 2018

The man @BirdDoggArt wrote it best! “I am pleased to finally share another set of vessels with you guys. As well as delving into ancient vessels of other cultures, I had the idea that we, too, may be defined in the future by our "vessels"... The people of 2500 will wonder what the hell we were up to... well, our art form is not only evolving the glass medium like at no other time in history, it is also happening in conjunction with a social awakening of consciousness and a cultural revolution as it pertains to marijuana. These are vessels of my own design, loosely modeled after a basic vase shape. I call them #funnelvases . They are simple in form, complex in design, with superb function and timeless longevity. Much love to my homie and amazing photographer @hubbardsteve for helping me document these pieces and countless others!! 🙏💪📸💓 Thanks for looking, and have an awesome day!”
.
.
.
.
.

Since the time of ancient Egyptians to the Roman Empire, the sun has been worshipped as a God. On the reverse of this coin, Sol the sun god is standing facing left, naked, wearing a radiate crown, a cloak draped over his shoulder, raising right hand & a globe in left hand.
